ch.iserver.ace.util
Class CallerThreadDomain

java.lang.Object
  ch.iserver.ace.util.CallerThreadDomain
All Implemented Interfaces:
ThreadDomain
public class CallerThreadDomain
extends Object
implements ThreadDomain

CallerThreadDomain does not create worker threads at all. It does not wrap the target instances either. It simply returns the target from the wrap(Object, Class) method and thus method calls on the target are processed on the caller thread.

Note, this might especially be useful in unit testing scenarios where threading introduces a degree of non-deterministic behavior.
